    "synopsis": "The Horus Heresy is broken, and the traitor legions scatter before a vengeful Imperium. The World Eaters are leaderless — their primarch Angron vanished, their greatest champion Kharn lost in a coma — and the Butcher's Nails drive the survivors to ever more savage slaughter. Desperate for fresh blood and a place to rebuild, the Legion fleet descends on a world near the Eye of Terror, only to find the remnants of the Emperor's Children already there. Told largely through Captain Dreagher of the Ninth and Skoral, a human medicae thrall, Anthony Reynolds charts the bloody decline of a Legion devouring itself in the days before the infamous battle of Skalathrax.",
